<br>
I've participated in a few small-group killings of these mobs and a few others. Every time it's a spur-of-the-moment &quot;we're bored and have time&quot; kind of thing. They're never planned, and whether or not we kill them really depends on whether we can scrounge up a group or two of people who aren't too tired from the day's raid. With that said, it's pretty much impossible for us to join a rotation on these mobs, because 80% of the time it comes up to &quot;our turn&quot; we won't be ready to kill him (We'll be too tired from raid, we won't have a tank on who wants to come, etc. Believe it or not most AD members don't want to kill Velious mobs... it was difficult enough for me to convince 3 groups to do Seru). That may be really good for you, but from our perspective, it's awfully unfair. You'd have the same rate of success by telling us to stop killing the mobs completely.<br>
<br>
I also respect your point of view Mearis and as an ex-officer of a Velious level guild I understand how fierce the spawn competition is. But I do feel that you coming here and basically shoving your rotation in our face and saying &quot;you have to accept this because Wudan and MiM did&quot; is disrespectful. Now you've got half your guild here with puppy eyes.<br>
<br>
Like Adell said, if AD happens to kill one of your mobs, then hopefully you'll give the guild whom we &quot;stole&quot; it from another chance in 3 days after respawn. I honestly cannot see how AD could join your rotation without dicking themselves over. <p>-Morb</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morbrz>MorbRZ</A> at: 6/23/03 6:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(6/23/03 8:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> Right, Gsam, I agree that some mobs are trivial enough that any attempt to rotate them is stupid - but I think with the exception of ST you'll admit, that none of the mobs we were particularly concerned with people 6 manning can be done with 6 people.  Tormax *might* be done by 12 superbly geared AD people but I doubt, and I doubt it takes any less than three groups or so do those, and as such they are a bit more of a coordinated effort.  As much as I'd like to see Dozekar and Statue rotated, those mobs are so easy that attempting to legislate them is asking for trouble.<br>
<br>
I entirely agree that if a guild left a mob all the way until it arrived to you, then they deserve to lose it, the problem is that often times the mob does not spawn until its way past our bedtime (or raidtime) and it only spawns after all the guild has logged off, and as such we get no real attempt at it.  I have no qualms *whatsoever* about losing a mob that we could have had an attempt at, if we didn't get it, its our fault, but the very idea behind a 24 hour grace period, which is standard practice in all rotations is that even with the random timer associated with them, you will get a shot at the mob at your timezone.<br>
<br>
Morb, the idea that within 24 hours of Tormax spawning, AD could not both do its event and drop Tormax or Cursed is a bit absurd <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   There's enough AD members to kill all those mobs anytime from 4 EST till 2 EST every day, and I have yet to see a day where AD raids that long.<br>
<br>
As I said, the danger is not losing one mob, that's not a problem at all, if anything its a minor setback.  What is VERY VERY disruptive is how much of a morale killer it is to have your entire guild log in to attempt a special mob, only to have it killed before your guild logs in.<br>
<br>
We had Avatar of War planned a few weeks ago, but Bollix informed me that they had that same event planned for several weeks now, and that several guildmates had logged in specifically for that.  We had farmed the previous 3 AoW, but could have very easily killed it well before Bollix's guild got online, and probably would have been several weeks before they would have gotten another shot, but we yielded.<br>
<br>
The only reason I brought up MiM and Wudan adhering to the rotation, is because they are in exactly the same situation as AD as far as those mobs go (I think King Tormax is equally trivial to both Wudan/MiM/AD for the sake of argument, and both raid at roughly the same times) but those two guilds both decided to honour our rotation.  We have no 'authority' to impose a rotation on AD, but hopefully by explanining our rational in detail people can understand why we are so hung up on it.<br>
<br>
RZ is a relatively low population server, there is not that much competition, and there's so many FFA targets that a guild could hit after their regular e-plane raid without interfering in anyone's rotation - some examples:<br>
<br>
Griegs<br>
Rumblecrush<br>
Doomshade<br>
Eashen/Ikatiar<br>
Dozekar<br>
Velkeltor<br>
Ring War<br>
Dain<br>
Yelinak<br>
Vindicator<br>
Statue of RZ<br>
Rhags/Archlich<br>
High Priest<br>
Seru<br>
Itraer VIus<br>
<br>
Etch... I could fill pages - the mobs that are meant to be protected by the rotation are mobs that are 'stepping stones' for guilds try to progress, unfortunately, those are obviously the mobs that drops the best twink/recruit gear.  And this doesn't even include any of the rotated mobs becoming FFA. <br>
<br>
Anyway, as I said, I have no authority to impose any rotation, but I have already tried explaining my view point repeatedly, and why several other guilds in your position have adhered to it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, so far its been pretty civil so I am happy to discuss my position further,<br>
<br>
Mearis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(6/23/03 7:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> ADD:<br>
