I represent LoTF for rotations and what I quoted from Mearis is the point blank idea of this thread.  If we lose a mob within 24 hours of it spawning then that is our fault.  Would it be difficult to ask that you wait 24 hours (aka grace period) after such mob has spawned so that the guild who is currently up on rotation has a chance to kill it before it is taken by someone else? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morbrz>MorbRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Asshole, P.I.</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#333333>(6/23/03 9:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> Huh? I didn't edit it out. <p>-Morb</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taranna>Taranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>HiElf Snob</span><br>  Posts: 834<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/03 12:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> Couple of points.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Of course, i could try to shame you into it, by asking what a guild that just killed xegony could possibly hope to gain by slumming it in Kael <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well for a start- most PoP high end encounters are ridiculously number-intensive.  They're also long and often punishing events.  Tormax on the other hand, is relatively trivial to access and requires almost no effort to kill.  As Gsam said, quite a few members (particularly those new to guild) can benefit from items these mobs drop.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What is VERY VERY disruptive is how much of a morale killer it is to have your entire guild log in to attempt a special mob, only to have it killed before your guild logs in<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and there's so many FFA targets that a guild could hit (list) <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Many of the mobs in that list have as good loot as any of the rotated mobs- plus BoT minis that spawn more frequently and aren't even rotated.  We've logged in a number of times, even gathered at Fennin once only to be told to go hit another zone.  We weren't particularly frustrated etc, because if the drops are roughly equivalent it's not an issue.<br>
<br>
Those statements above are therefore conflicting- I'm not sure how it's frustrating to find a single mob killed when as you say, there are so many uncontested mobs up.  Now if those mobs drop loot as good, or nearly as good- this is a bit of a non-issue.<br>
<br>
I think the crux of the matter is the accessibility of the mobs in question matched versus their reward.  It isn't realistic for a small group of AD to clear all the way through Griegs for loot that isn't worth the trouble.  Likewise for the ringwar and Dain- takes a lot more effort that, after hard elemental sessions most ppl just can't put in.  Cursed and Tormaxx are both very accessible, easily killed with a relatively small crew and are fantastic risk/reward.  <br>
<br>
With random spawns it's really luck of the draw when it pops- and it certainly isn't after every event that a small group of guildies goes after these mobs.  So in terms of the odds of something like this happening- it's a very low chance- it needs to pop in a relatively small time window *and* we have to be willing to muster ourselves to go after it.  Plus, as has been said, RZ is hardly a highly contested spawn server, and there are simply loads of targets out there- including BoT minis that now drop loot better than Tormax far more frequently, and spawn every 8 hours- so why the big fuss over the occasional Tormax or Cursed kill?  In terms of progression- Cursed and Tormax gain a guild nothing- the only 'essential' loots for progression are BF's off cursed perhaps.<br>
<br>
Progression mobs from Velious/early Luclin are Emp, VT mobs and PoP flag tier- those grant passage to the high end game, not repeated farmage of Cursed etc <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I understand people's frustration at the pace of farming- but the point's been done to death I think, that there are more than enough loot-droppers out there uncontested.  Not saying that the occasional disruption of an established rotation is inconsequential- but it's certainly not a huge inconvenience given the content available.<br>
<br>
