<br>
Heck, I am sure AD back when Velious content was cutting edge, probably farmed at least over 20 King Tormax.  How many of those people still use the boots they got?  110 mana FT 2 boots are nearly unmatched until Emperor, and, assuming they are upgrade they can be passed on.  It is in fact very very easy after you have gotten better boots than WDS, to turn them back into Yelinak for a 'droppable' helm, then give the droppable helm to the needy recruit, and then have the recruit request the helm with Yelinak for boots.<br>
<br>
I am not denying people the chance to get gear for twinks, heck, twinks are some of the most fun you can have in this game, but there's so much gear you can upgrade for twinks without touch rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
And Tar as I said, there are a lot of targets, but none of them do drop equivalent loot to Tormax.  While you can progress fine through Velious and SoL without Tormax loot, I am sure if people could pick TWO Velious mobs to farm at the expense of all others, they would be Tormax and Avatar of War, because most of their drops have no logical replacement.  Tormax drops THE best hat in game for most melee classes, the best caster boots in game, A ST key, the best melee boots in game, one of the best wisdom caster belts in game.... etch.  Tormax is a quick even, but Ikatiar, Eashen, Dozekar, those are as fast if not faster, with new pathing literally any class can pull Iki/Eashen to zone in.<br>
<br>
Heck, Cursed cycle is by far the most time consuming raid SoD does, but we are glad to do it whenever we can, because the loot returned is just so very good (drop some !%! BF though!!)<br>
<br>
In terms of progression to the higher game, yes, PoP flags and Emperor mark 'gatekeeper' mobs, but in terms of gear progression, Cursed/Tormax are as important, otherwise with that logic people would kill Fennin only once, maybe twice to flag the entire guild, instead people kill it non stop, because the increase in HP and DPS from Fennin loot is very considerable.<br>
<br>
Finally, yes, we have had to 'give up' on a target sometime, because the mob hadn't spawned yet, and its an entirely different situation, because you know the mob will be there tomorrow, and its just random chance.  Imagine if instead of Fennin being called, because the Guardian of Doomfire spawned late, Fennin would be called because Wudan killed it earlier in the raid time, after their regular raid because : &quot;With random spawns it's really luck of the draw when it pops- and it certainly isn't after every event that a small group of guildies goes after these mobs&quot;.<br>
<br>
Would the reaction be the same, and would people be willing to go do another event? :P  (don't answer that, hehe) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morbrz>MorbRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Asshole, P.I.</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/03 7:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> Revered never even was able to take a shot at Zlandicar because Eternal Shadows permacamped him. We only got one shot at Tormax, and that was a day before the guild broke up because a number of guilds kept him dead; and even at our attempt 35 Reverant jerks were standing behind us waiting to wipe so they could take him. Whether ES or AD or Thunderblade's Heroes killed the mobs before us, they still beat us there, and although it sucked for us, I didn't go to their boards and bitch. Sorry; I feel your pain, but I still disagree with you. <p>-Morb</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takrolimus>Takrolimus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/03 12:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> I for one find it kind of funny (although commendable) that on RZ of all places, we have such a nice hugs'n kisses rotation system. I mean on Blue servers, there is tremendous cockblocking and/or griefing of content simply because they are much more crowded and there are no real pvp consequences.<br>
