<br>
The difference is that until recently, nobody had tried to establish a rotation on lower tier mobs.  Until we made an effort to establish this rotation, we never evern raised a hair if someone got the mobs before us, heck, to this day we haven't gotten Dozekar for the past two months, but even though its been usually farmed by a crew of MiM, I haven't ever complained about it.  There's a key difference in a rotation encompassing all mobs able to kill a mob, except one key partner, and losing a mob that nobody has even thought of rotating.<br>
<br>
The reason we 'formed' this rotation, is so guilds wouldn't behave like hawks and wait for people to wipe so they could take the mob.  We are a European guild, the spawns usually work in our favour, and with Reverant and ES breaking up, if we wanted we could do a damn good job hogging all Velious and easy Luclin content, yet we are making the best effort we can to share the mobs evenly.<br>
<br>
If you notice what I posted, it isn't the setback in waiting one week/nearest patch in getting the mobs that's the annoying part, its the fact that it makes scheduling mobs a logistical nightmare for me.  Hell, before Reverant finally agreed to a rotation, CE, CN, CoTW didn't stand a chance in hell of seeing Tormax alive, because we'd rush to kill it whenever it spawned, half of the reason we wanted to impose this rotation, is to give newer guilds a chance to try out this content.  In an FFA system, new guilds would never ever get a chance to try those mobs, instead with a scheduled rotation, as long as they show they are capable of killing those mobs, they are given 24 hours free to throw bodies at him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blizzyy>Blizzyy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Powernap</span><br>  Posts: 921<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/03 2:10 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/blizzard/fullsize/playboy_1001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: requesting consideration for lower level guild rotations</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I think all but three spawns that I know off in the last 6 months have been farmed by Tetzou with a few friends, and that's a LOT of Zlandicars.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
